**Phase 5.2: Touch-first quiz** — committed and tagged `phase-5.2-touch-first-quiz`. Build and typecheck pass.

### What was implemented:

| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Swipe navigation** | Custom `useSwipe` hook using native touch events (zero new deps). Swipe-right = back, swipe-left = advance on multi-select. `touch-pan-y` preserves vertical scroll. |
| **Full-screen immersive** | All quiz containers use `100dvh` instead of `100vh`, eliminating layout jumps from mobile browser chrome. |
| **Haptic + tap feedback** | `navigator.vibrate(10)` on option taps and navigation. `active:scale-[0.97]` press effect on all interactive elements. |
| **Compact progress** | Mobile: dot indicator with elongated pill for active step. Desktop: thin bar unchanged. Both fixed-top with backdrop blur. |
| **Sticky CTA** | Results page: fixed bottom bar on mobile with Refresh/Retake buttons + safe-area padding. Content padded to avoid overlap. |
| **Bonus** | Result thumbnails migrated `<img>` → `next/image`. Navigation buttons now sticky at bottom with gradient fade for thumb reach. Directional slide animation (left vs right). |

### Files changed:
- **New**: `apps/web/hooks/use-swipe.ts`
- **Modified**: `app/quiz/page.tsx`, `components/quiz/quiz-step.tsx`, `components/quiz/quiz-results.tsx`, `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`
